## L1.8 — SLAs & Metrics

> **TTL Note**: SLA numbers are volatile and MUST be annotated. Tool URLs also require TTL.

{% for metric in METRICS %}
### {{metric.name}}

- **Type**: {{metric.type}}
- **Target**: {{metric.target}}<!-- TTL: @valid_until={{SLA_TTL}} -->
- **Source**: {{metric.source}}
{% if metric.type == "threshold" %}
- **Threshold**: {{metric.threshold.operator}} {{metric.threshold.value}} {{metric.threshold.unit}}
- **Monitoring**: {{metric.threshold.monitoring_frequency}}
{% endif %}
{% if metric.related_invariant %}
- **Related Invariants**: {{metric.related_invariant | join(", ")}}
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}

---

## L1.9 — Scope Boundaries

### In Scope

{% for item in IN_SCOPE %}
- {{item}}
{% endfor %}

### Out of Scope

{% for item in OUT_OF_SCOPE %}
- **{{item.description}}**
  - Reference Type: {{item.reference.type}}
  - Target: {{item.reference.target}}
{% if item.reference.handoff_event %}
  - Handoff: `{{item.reference.handoff_event.from_step}}` → `{{item.reference.handoff_event.to_step}}` via {{item.reference.handoff_event.mechanism}}
  - Handoff SLA: {{item.reference.handoff_event.sla}}
  - Failure Recovery: {{item.reference.handoff_event.failure_recovery}}
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
